Package: SSDbain
Type: Package
Date: 2021-11-1
Title: Sample Size Determination using AAFBF for Bayesian Hypothesis Testing Implemented in bain 
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Qianrao","Fu",email="q.fu@uu.nl",role=c("aut","cre"))
Description: Computes the required sample size using approximated adjusted fractional Bayes factors (AAFBF)
            for equality, inequality, unconstrained  and complement hypotheses.
            Functions to compute the sample size within Bayesian framework. The statistical underpinnings are
    described in 
    Fu, Hoijtink, and Moerbeek,(2021) <DOI: 10.3758/s13428-020-01408-1>,
    Fu, Moerbeek, and Hoijtink,(2021) <DOI: 10.31234/osf.io/ymvb9>, and
    Fu, (2021) <DOI:10.1037/met0000187>.
License: GPL (> =3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.6.3),
    stats
